<p>I have a <strong>WPF</strong> <code>Window</code> with a <code>DataGrid</code> inside a <code>Grid</code> like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Window x:Class="WpfApplication1.MainWindow"         xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"         xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"         Title="MainWindow" SizeToContent="WidthAndHeight" WindowStyle="ToolWindow" ResizeMode="NoResize"&gt;     &lt;Grid&gt;         &lt;Grid.ColumnDefinitions&gt;             &lt;ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/&gt;         &lt;/Grid.ColumnDefinitions&gt;          &lt;Grid.RowDefinitions&gt;             &lt;RowDefinition Height="Auto"/&gt;             &lt;RowDefinition Height="Auto"/&gt;         &lt;/Grid.RowDefinitions&gt;          &lt;TextBlock FontSize="20"&gt;Some header with some pretty longish text&lt;/TextBlock&gt;          &lt;DataGrid Grid.Row="1" Height="200"&gt;             &lt;DataGrid.Columns&gt;                 &lt;DataGridTextColumn Header="Column1" Width="*"/&gt;             &lt;/DataGrid.Columns&gt;         &lt;/DataGrid&gt;      &lt;/Grid&gt; &lt;/Window&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I'd like the <code>DataGrid</code>'s width to be at least the width of the <code>TextBlock</code>, which in this case is, because of the <code>Grid</code>'s <code>ColumnDefinition</code>'s width set to <code>Auto</code>.</p>  <p>But somehow, the width of the <code>DataGrid</code>'s <code>Column</code> is at a minimum (and can't even be resized), while I expect it's width to be filled. Currently it looks like this:<br> <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/6LtEt.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/6LtEt.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Note that the window has to be a <code>ToolWindow</code> and it's <code>SizeToContent</code> set to <code>WidthAndHeight</code>.</p>